1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,720
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:05,720
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:05,720 --> 00:00:06,720
Hi everyone.
大家好。

4
00:00:06,720 --> 00:00:07,720
My name is Catherine.
我是Catherine。

5
00:00:07,720 --> 00:00:08,720
What do you got, Catherine, for us today?
Catherine，你今天给我们带来了什么？

6
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:09,720
That's a good question.
这是个好问题。

7
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:12,880
Well, we've got a little bit of a Seinfeld situation.
嗯，我们有一个有点像《宋飞正传》里的情景。

8
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:17,240
So, for those of you who are not familiar with this American TV show, which, by the
所以，对于那些不熟悉这部美国电视剧的朋友们，顺便说一句，

9
00:00:17,240 --> 00:00:24,640
way, is one of my favorites, Seinfeld is a TV show, a comedy, about very awkward, very
这是我最喜欢的剧之一，《宋飞正传》是一部喜剧，讲的是一些非常尴尬、

10
00:00:24,640 --> 00:00:27,840
common situations that are taken to the extreme.
非常常见但被夸张到极致的情景。

11
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:28,840
Right.
没错。

12
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:30,560
So, it's a very popular show.
所以，这是一部非常受欢迎的剧。

13
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:33,040
It was around for like 10 years, I think.
它大概播了十年左右，我想。

14
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:34,040
Oh, yeah.
哦，是的。

15
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:35,040
But it's not airing anymore.
但现在不再播出了。

16
00:00:35,040 --> 00:00:36,800
Well, they're not making new episodes anymore.
嗯，他们不再制作新剧集了。

17
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,680
No, you have to see them in reruns.
不，你只能在重播里看到它们。

18
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:39,680
Reruns, right.
重播，没错。

19
00:00:39,680 --> 00:00:44,720
So, we have a situation that's very common and it was pretty funny on the show.
所以，我们有一个非常常见的情景，在剧里还挺搞笑的。

20
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:47,400
It's a guy trying to rent a car.
是一个男人想租车。

21
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:52,960
Okay, so he's probably at the airport or traveling and he's had a long flight and he wants to
好的，所以他可能是在机场或者旅行中，刚经历长途飞行，想

22
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:55,680
rent a car, but of course, there are some problems.
租辆车，但当然，遇到了一些问题。

23
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:58,360
So, this is an elementary level lesson, by the way.
顺便说一下，这是一个初级水平的课程。

24
00:00:58,360 --> 00:01:03,000
So keep that in mind as we listen to this dialogue one time.
所以在我们听一遍这段对话时，请记住这一点。

25
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:09,480
Hi, I made a reservation for a mid-size vehicle.
你好，我预订了一辆中型车。

26
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:11,680
The name is Jimmy Fox.
名字是Jimmy Fox。

27
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:16,000
I'm sorry, we have no mid-size available at the moment.
抱歉，我们现在没有中型车可用。

28
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,440
I don't understand.
我不明白。

29
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:18,840
I made a reservation.
我预订了。

30
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:21,040
Do you have my reservation?
你们有我的预订记录吗？

31
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:24,080
Yes, we do.
是的，我们有。

32
00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:27,720
Unfortunately, we ran out of cars.
不幸的是，我们的车都租完了。

33
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:31,160
But the reservation keeps the car here.
但预订应该能保留车在这里。

34
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:33,200
That's why you have the reservation.
这就是为什么要有预订。

35
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:36,200
I know why we have reservations.
我知道为什么要有预订。

36
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,040
I don't think you do.
我觉得你不知道。

37
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:39,880
If you did, I'd have a car.
如果你知道，我就该有车了。

38
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:42,680
See, you know how to take the reservation.
你看，你知道怎么接受预订。

39
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:46,700
You just don't know how to hold the reservation and that's really the most important part
你就是不知道怎么保留预订，而这才是预订最重要的部分，

40
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:49,000
of the reservation, the holding.
保留。

41
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Anybody can just take them.
谁都能接受预订。

42
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:55,000
But we do have a compact or an SUV if you'd like.
但我们有紧凑型车或SUV，如果你想要的话。

43
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,120
Fine.
好吧。

44
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,840
I'll take the compact.
我就要紧凑型车。

45
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,240
All right.
好的。

46
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:02,680
We have a blue Ford Focus for you, Mr. Fox.
我们有一辆蓝色福特福克斯给您，Fox先生。

47
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,160
Would you like insurance?
您要买保险吗？

48
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:09,680
Yeah, you better give me the insurance because I'm going to beat the hell out of this car.
是的，你最好给我保险，因为我要把这车往死里开。

49
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:14,720
All right, great.
好的，没问题。

50
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:16,520
So this actually happens a lot.
所以这种情况其实经常发生。

51
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:21,800
You make a reservation and either they lose it or they run out of cars.
你做了预订，要么他们弄丢了，要么车租完了。

52
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,920
It's such a common situation.
这真是个常见的情况。

53
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:25,520
And it's not just cars.
而且不只是车。

54
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:28,800
Sometimes this happens at restaurants too and it really makes me angry.
有时餐厅也会这样，这真的让我很生气。

55
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:29,800
Yeah, that happens a lot.
是啊，经常发生。

56
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:32,080
You show up and they're like, oh, we don't have a reservation.
你到了，他们就说，哦，我们没有你的预订。

57
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:33,480
And you're just like...
然后你就只能……

58
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:35,760
Well, then you have to keep yourself in check.
嗯，那你得控制住自己。

59
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:36,840
You can't really get angry.
你不能真的生气。

60
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:37,840
But this guy does.
但这个人就生气了。

61
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:42,100
So let's take a look at the language takeaway to find out what are some of the words we're
所以让我们看看语言要点，找出我们在这里用来描述租车

62
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:49,200
using here to describe renting a car and what kind of car we're talking about.
以及谈论车型的一些词汇。

63
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,600
Language takeaway.
语言要点。

64
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:57,080
Well, as you mentioned, at rental places, they have different size cars, right?
嗯，正如你提到的，在租车公司，他们有不同大小的车，对吧？

65
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,080
Different size vehicles.
不同大小的车辆。

66
00:02:58,080 --> 00:03:00,400
Which, by the way, costs different prices.
顺便说一下，价格也不同。

67
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,400
Right.
没错。

68
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:05,040
So let's take a look at the sizes that they mentioned in dialogue.
所以让我们看看对话中提到的车型大小。

69
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:10,160
Starting with the cheapest one, the least expensive and the smallest, it's a compact
从最便宜的、最便宜也最小的开始，是紧凑型

70
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:11,160
vehicle.
车辆。

71
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,160
All right, compact.
好的，紧凑型。

72
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:14,440
So compact actually means small.
所以compact实际上意思是小的。

73
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:15,440
Small.
小的。

74
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,440
Right.
没错。

75
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:17,880
So compact car, you're going to hear very often.
所以紧凑型车，你会经常听到。

76
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:21,680
Even if you're buying a car, let's think of an...
即使你买车，让我们想想一个……

77
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:23,200
What's a compact car?
什么是紧凑型车？

78
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:26,720
The VW Golf is a compact car, very small car.
大众高尔夫就是紧凑型车，非常小的车。

79
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:31,560
So usually it's two doors or if it's a four door car, it's very small, not very long,
所以通常是两门，或者如果是四门车，也很小，不太长，

80
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,560
right?
对吧？

81
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,560
Right, exactly.
对，没错。

82
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:36,080
So maybe like a Ford Focus could be a small car, a compact.
所以比如福特福克斯可能算小型车，紧凑型。

83
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:40,240
Now moving up in size a little bit, we would have a midsize vehicle.
现在稍微大一点，我们有中型车辆。

84
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,440
Okay, midsize vehicle is...
好的，中型车辆是……

85
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:45,600
Well, it's a giveaway here because mid means middle.
嗯，这很明显，因为mid意思是中间。

86
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,240
So it's kind of in the middle between the small and the large.
所以它介于小型和大型之间。

87
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:50,960
And this is your average four door sedan car.
这就是你常见的四门轿车。

88
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:51,960
Okay.
好的。

89
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:57,360
So as an example, you would have a Ford Taurus or maybe a Toyota Camry.
举个例子，比如福特金牛座或者丰田凯美瑞。

90
00:03:57,360 --> 00:04:00,920
Yeah, Toyota Camry is maybe the most common car.
是的，丰田凯美瑞可能是最常见的车。

91
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:01,920
Yeah.
嗯。

92
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:04,800
It's kind of expensive, but it's still midsize, right?
它有点贵，但还是中型车，对吧？

93
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:05,800
Exactly.
没错。

94
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:10,360
And now a bigger car and probably one of the most popular cars in the United States is
而现在更大的车，可能是美国最受欢迎的车之一，是

95
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,760
an SUV.
SUV。

96
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:12,760
Not anymore, Marco.
现在不是了，Marco。

97
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:13,760
I know.
我知道。

98
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:16,040
Yeah, the energy crisis and the...
是啊，能源危机和……

99
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,040
Gas prices.
油价。

100
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:19,080
Well, and the economy as well.
嗯，还有经济因素。

101
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:21,000
People are not driving their SUVs anymore.
人们不再开他们的SUV了。

102
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,020
But SUV is an acronym.
但SUV是一个首字母缩写。

103
00:04:23,020 --> 00:04:25,120
That means it stands for three different words.
意思是它代表三个不同的单词。

104
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:26,120
S meaning...
S代表……

105
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,120
Sports.
运动。

106
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,120
U meaning...
U代表……

107
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,120
Utility.
多功能。

108
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,120
V...
V……

109
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,120
Vehicle.
车辆。

110
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,120
All right.
好的。

111
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,120
Thank you.
谢谢。

112
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,440
So SUV, sport utility vehicle, means it can go maybe off-road.
所以SUV，运动型多功能车，意味着它可以越野。

113
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,440
Right.
没错。

114
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:39,120
So an example of this would be a Ford Explorer or...
举个例子，比如福特探险者或者……

115
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,120
Jeep Cherokee.
吉普切诺基。

116
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,960
A Jeep Cherokee could be an SUV as well.
吉普切诺基也可以是SUV。

117
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:43,960
That's right.
没错。

118
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:45,000
Those are three different types of cars.
这是三种不同类型的车。

119
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:49,040
Now obviously there are many more like a van or a...
现在显然还有很多其他类型，比如面包车或者……

120
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,040
A limo.
豪华轿车。

121
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,920
A limo, like a limousine.
一辆豪华轿车，就像 limousine 那种。

122
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:56,400
But yeah, these are the most common ones that you would rent at a car rental place.
不过，这些是你在租车公司最常租到的车型。

123
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,720
Yeah, definitely.
没错，确实如此。

124
00:04:57,720 --> 00:05:02,120
But what we have to do here is make a reservation.
但我们现在要做的是预订。

125
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,720
Now interesting, you make a reservation.
有意思，你说“make a reservation”。

126
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,280
Yeah, you don't have it.
对，你还没有车。

127
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:07,280
You don't do it.
你不是“做”车。

128
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,740
You don't...
你不是……

129
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:09,740
You make it.
你是“做”预订。

130
00:05:09,740 --> 00:05:10,740
Yeah, you make...
对，你“做”……

131
00:05:10,740 --> 00:05:12,080
These are words that go together.
这些是固定搭配的词。

132
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:14,000
So we're going to keep them together.
所以我们要把它们放在一起记。

133
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,480
I can call a restaurant.
我可以给餐厅打电话。

134
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:17,480
So say for example, Marco works at a restaurant.
比如说，Marco 在一家餐厅工作。

135
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:20,240
I say, hello, I'd like to make a reservation for tonight.
我说，你好，我想预订今晚的位子。

136
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,240
Oh, okay.
哦，好的。

137
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:22,240
Perfect.
完美。

138
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,880
Now if you show up at the restaurant, you say...
如果你到了餐厅，你说……

139
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:25,880
Where's my table?
我的桌子呢？

140
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:27,680
I made a reservation.
我预订过了。

141
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,680
Right.
对。

142
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:32,680
And of course I throw a fit because there's no table for me.
当然我会大发脾气，因为没给我留桌子。

143
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:36,280
So you make a reservation and in this case it was made before.
所以你“make a reservation”，而且这次是提前预订的。

144
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:38,240
Okay, so you make a reservation.
好的，所以是“make a reservation”。

145
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:41,360
Now why was this guy angry at the rental car place?
那这个人为什么在租车公司生气？

146
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:48,040
Oh, long story short, the company ran out of cars.
哦，长话短说，公司没车了。

147
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:51,760
Not all cars, just the car that he wanted, the mid-size vehicle.
不是所有车，只是他想要的那种中型车。

148
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:53,560
So they ran out.
所以他们“ran out”了。

149
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,600
So that doesn't mean they're actually running somewhere.
但这不意味着他们真的在跑步。

150
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:58,880
No, they're not putting on their running shoes and going for a jog.
不，他们没穿上跑鞋去慢跑。

151
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:04,680
Now in this case, to run out or in this case, we ran out means that they don't have any
在这个例子里，“run out”或“we ran out”意思是他们没有……

152
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:05,680
more.
更多了。

153
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:06,680
You don't have any more.
你没有了。

154
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,680
Exactly.
完全正确。

155
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:12,720
So, I think it is a nice word for us to take a look at some other examples now.
所以，我觉得这是个好词，我们来看看其他例子。

156
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:13,720
Example one.
例子一。

157
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:17,080
We're going to run out of gasoline.
我们的汽油快用完了。

158
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:23,400
We need to find a gas station soon.
我们得尽快找个加油站。

159
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:26,680
Example two.
例子二。

160
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,560
Can you buy some milk on your way home?
你能在回家的路上买点牛奶吗？

161
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:33,320
We ran out last night.
我们昨晚用完了。

162
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:35,640
Example three.
例子三。

163
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:36,640
My pen ran out of ink.
我的笔没墨了。

164
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:40,440
Can you lend me one, please?
能借我一支吗？

165
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:45,280
Not a fun phrase, but an important one in case you're ever in a restaurant or in a hotel
这不是个有趣的短语，但很重要，万一你在餐厅、酒店或任何可以购买或租东西的地方，东西全没了。

166
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:49,800
or in a place where you can purchase something or rent something and it's all gone.
全没了。

167
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,800
All right.
好的。

168
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:53,880
So, I think we've taken a look at a lot of great words here.
所以，我觉得我们看了很多好词。

169
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,120
So let's listen to this dialogue again.
那我们再听一遍这段对话。

170
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:59,680
We're going to slow it down just a little bit and then we'll come back and explain some
我们会稍微放慢速度，然后回来解释一些……

171
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,680
phrases.
短语。

172
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:07,880
Hi, I made a reservation for a mid-size vehicle.
你好，我预订了一辆中型车。

173
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,680
The name is Jimmy Fox.
名字是 Jimmy Fox。

174
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:11,000
I'm sorry.
抱歉。

175
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,000
